.TH WIN31X 1 "July 17, 2026" "win31x 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
win31x \- a minimal Windows 3.1-inspired window manager for X11
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B win31x
.RI [ --display " display" ]
.RI [ --help ]
.RI [ --version ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Win31 X
is a small reparenting window manager intended to run as the only window
manager in an Xorg session.  It draws classic beveled frames, places minimized
applications on the desktop as clickable icons, and provides an Applications
desktop icon backed by installed freedesktop desktop entries.  A Control Panel
desktop icon provides Wi-Fi, color-scheme, and automatic screen-lock settings.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR --display " " DISPLAY
Connect to DISPLAY instead of the value in the
.B DISPLAY
environment variable.
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Show command-line help.
.TP
.BR -v , " --version"
Show the program version.
.SH DESKTOP CONTROLS
Click the Applications icon once to open the launcher.  Select an application
with the pointer or arrow keys and double-click it, or press Enter, to start it.
Escape closes the launcher.  The mouse wheel and Page Up/Page Down scroll it.
.PP
Click the Control Panel icon once to open it.  Wi-Fi can refresh the visible
NetworkManager networks, connect to a selected open or personal WPA/SAE
network, and disconnect the active network.  Colors applies one of five desktop
and active-title schemes immediately.  Auto Lock can enable or disable idle
locking, select a 1, 5, 10, 15, 30, 60, or 120 minute preset, or lock
immediately.  Color and auto-lock changes are saved automatically.
.PP
Use the underscore button in a title bar to minimize a window.  Its desktop
icon restores it with one click.  Drag a title bar to move a window, drag an
outer border to resize it, and use the X button to request that it close.
Clicking any inactive application focuses and raises it; transient dialogs
remain above their owning application.  The activating pointer press is also
delivered to the application.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.TP
.B Alt+Tab
Focus and raise the next visible application.
.TP
.B Alt+F2
Open the Applications window.
.TP
.B Alt+F4
Close the active application.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DISPLAY
X server to use.
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME, XDG_DATA_DIRS
Locations searched for application desktop entries.
.TP
.B WIN31X_TERMINAL
Executable used to launch desktop entries marked Terminal=true.  It must
accept the conventional \-e option.  If unset, Win31 X searches for
x-terminal-emulator, xterm, uxterm, foot, or kitty.
.TP
.B WIN31X_ICON_DIR
Directory containing the required supplied PNG icon set.  This is primarily
useful for development and tests; installed sessions use the packaged icon
directory.
.TP
.B WIN31X_NMCLI
Absolute path to the nmcli executable.  The installed default is
.IR /usr/bin/nmcli .
This override is primarily useful for tests or nonstandard local installations.
.TP
.B WIN31X_XSS_LOCK
Absolute path to the xss-lock executable.  The installed default is
.IR /usr/bin/xss-lock .
.TP
.B WIN31X_LOCKER
Absolute path to the screen-locker executable.  The installed default is
.IR /usr/bin/xsecurelock .
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME, HOME
Determine the location of the per-user Win31 X settings file.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/applications/*.desktop
System application entries.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/applications/*.desktop
Per-user application entries.
.TP
.I /usr/share/win31x/icons/*.png
User-supplied application icon assets installed with Win31 X.
.TP
.I /usr/share/icons/hicolor/*/apps/win31x.png
Supplied Applications artwork used by display managers for the Win31 X session.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/win31x/settings.conf
Private per-user color and auto-lock settings.  When
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is unset, the path is
.IR ~/.config/win31x/settings.conf .
.SH CONTROL PANEL SERVICES
Wi-Fi requires NetworkManager and
.BR nmcli (1).
Supported connection types are open, OWE, WPA-PSK, and SAE personal networks;
enterprise and legacy WEP setup is left to NetworkManager's other front ends.
Wi-Fi passwords are masked on screen, are not included in process arguments or
log messages, and are supplied to nmcli through a private file descriptor.
.PP
Automatic locking requires
.BR xss-lock (1)
and a locker; Debian installations use
.BR xsecurelock (1).
Win31 X owns the X server idle timeout while running and restores the previous
X saver policy when it exits.  xss-lock also integrates locking with the login
session and system suspend path.
.PP
When the configured locker is xsecurelock, its password prompt displays one
asterisk for each entered character on both idle and immediate locks.  This
confirms keyboard input but intentionally reveals password length.
Authentication remains entirely within xsecurelock and PAM; Win31 X does not
handle the lock-screen password.
.SH DISPLAY REQUIREMENTS
The supplied-color icon renderer requires a TrueColor X visual.  Standard
modern Xorg configurations provide one.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR Xorg (1),
.BR nmcli (1),
.BR xss-lock (1),
.BR xsecurelock (1),
.BR startx (1),
.BR xterm (1)
